Program: Discovery
Title: Cosmic Questions - Part One
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxd6
Last Broadcast Date: 21 April 1999
A look at the conditions that existed before the dawn of time and space. The American Association for the Advancement of Science (AAAS) recently held a conference at the Smithsonian Institute entitled 'Cosmic Questions', examining the dawn of time in terms of both religion and science.